Laurie Bird https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laurie_Bird 0 Laurie Bird (September 26, 1953 – June 15, 1979) was an American film actress and photographer. She appeared in three films during the 1970s. Two of them were directed by Monte Hellman. She was romantically involved with Hellman and Art Garfunkel; committing suicide in the latter's apartment by taking an overdose of Valium. Bird inspired one of Tim Kinsella's novels. Laurie_Bird ( September_26_,_1953 – June_15_,_1979 ) was an_American_film_actress and photographer . She appeared in three_films during the_1970s .
